oleter Zrenjanin|Proleter Zrenjanin]]\n|win_RSB=18|draw_RSB=12|loss_RSB=4|gf_RSB=75|ga_RSB=30|status_RSB=C\n|win_DZA=20|draw_DZA=5|loss_DZA=9|gf_DZA=75|ga_DZA=33\n|win_PAR=13|draw_PAR=14|loss_PAR=7|gf_PAR=55|ga_PAR=40\n|win_VOJ=15|draw_VOJ=9|loss_VOJ=10|gf_VOJ=42|ga_VOJ=44\n|win_\u017dEL=15|draw_\u017dEL=8|loss_\u017dEL=11|gf_\u017dEL=51|ga_\u017dEL=38\n|win_HSP=11|draw_HSP=16|loss_HSP=7|gf_HSP=47|ga_HSP=38\n|win_RNI=12|draw_RNI=10|loss_RNI=12|gf_RNI=35|ga_RNI=36\n|win_VEL=9|draw_VEL=16|loss_VEL=9|gf_VEL=41|ga_VEL=45\n|win_\u010cEL=11|draw_\u010cEL=11|loss_\u010cEL=12|gf_\u010cEL=42|ga_\u010cEL=41\n|win_VAR=12|draw_VAR=9|loss_VAR=13|gf_VAR=37|ga_VAR=36\n|win_SAR=10|draw_SAR=13|loss_SAR=11|gf_SAR=38|ga_SAR=44\n|win_OLI=11|draw_OLI=11|loss_OLI=12|gf_OLI=32|ga_OLI=41\n|win_Bor=9|draw_Bor=13|loss_Bor=12|gf_Bor=35|ga_Bor=46\n|win_OFK=13|draw_OFK=4|loss_OFK=17|gf_OFK=43|ga_OFK=52\n|win_NKZ=11|draw_NKZ=7|loss_NKZ=16|gf_NKZ=41|ga_NKZ=59\n|win_MAR=7|draw_MAR=14|loss_MAR=13|gf_MAR=33|ga_MAR=57\n|win_RIJ=9|draw_RIJ=5|loss_RIJ=20|gf_RIJ=31|ga_RIJ=52|status_RIJ=R\n|win_PZR=7|draw_PZR=9|loss_PZR=18|gf_PZR=24|ga_PZR=45|status_PZR=R\n|col_EC=green1|text_EC=Qualification for [[1969\u201370 European Cup#First round|European Cup first round]]\n|result1=EC\n|col_ECWC=yellow1|text_ECWC=Qualification for [[1969\u201370 European Cup Winners' Cup#First round|Cup Winners' Cup first round]]\n|result2=ECWC\n|col_ICFC=blue1|text_ICFC=Qualification for [[1969\u201370 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup#First round|Inter-Cities Fairs Cup first round]]\n|result3=ICFC|result4=ICFC|result15= ICFC\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to [[Yugoslav Second League]]\n|result17=R|result18=R\n|update=complete\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesj/joeghist.html rsssf.com] \n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==See also==\n*[[1968\u201369 Yugoslav Second League]]\n*[[1968\u201369 Yugoslav Cup]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesj/joeghist.html Yugoslavia Domestic Football Full Tables]\n\n{{Yugoslav First League}}\n{{1968\u201369 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1968-69 Yugoslav First League}}\n[[Category:Yugoslav First League seasons]]\n[[Category:1968\u201369 in European association football leagues|Yugo]]\n[[Category:1968\u201369 in Yugoslavian football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Yugoslav First League|Prva savezna liga]]\n| season             = 1968&ndash;69\n| dates = {{Nowrap|18 August 1968 \u2013 7 July 1969}}\n| winners            = [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]] (9th title)\n| relegated          = [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]]<br />[[FK Proleter Zrenjanin|Proleter Zrenjanin]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1969\u201370 European Cup|European Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers =  [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[1969\u201370 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers =  [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n| continentalcup3    = [[1969\u201370 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup|Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers =  [[FK Partizan|Partizan]]<br>[[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]<br />[[NK Zagreb]]\n| league topscorer   = [[Vojin Lazarevi\u0107]] (22)\n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| longest wins       = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[1967\u201368 Yugoslav First League|1967\u201368]]\n| nextseason         = [[1969\u201370 Yugoslav First League|1969\u201370]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1968\u201369 [[Yugoslav First League]] season''' was the 23rd season of the First Federal League ({{lang-sh|Prva savezna liga}}), the top level [[association football]] league of [[SFR Yugoslavia]], since its establishment in 1946. Eighteen teams contested the competition, with [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]] winning their ninth national title.\n\n==Teams==\nDue to the expansion of the format from 16 to 18 teams at the end of the previous season no one was relegated. [[FK Bor|Bor]] and [[NK \u010celik Zenica|\u010celik]] were promoted from the 1967\u201368 [[Yugoslav Second League]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n!width=\"130\"| Team\n!width=\"100\"| Location\n!width=\"200\"| [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia#Federal subjects|Federal Republic]] \n!width=\"90\"| Position<br />in [[1967\u201368 Yugoslav First League|1967\u201368]]\n|-\n|[[FK Bor|Bor]]\n|[[Bor, Serbia|Bor]]\n|{{flag|SR Serbia}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|-\n|[[NK \u010celik Zenica|\u010celik]]\n|[[Zenica]]\n|{{flag|SR Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n|{{N/A}}\n|-\n|[[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n|[[Zagreb]]\n|{{flag|SR Croatia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<span style=\"display:none\">003</span>3rd\n|-\n|[[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]]\n|[[Split, Croatia|Split]]\n|{{flag|SR Croatia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<span style=\"display:none\">004</span>4th\n|-\n|[[NK Maribor|Maribor]]\n|[[Maribor]]\n|{{flag|SR Slovenia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<span style=\"display:none\">012</span>12th\n|-\n|[[OFK Beograd|OFK Belgrade]]\n|[[Belgrade]]\n|{{flag|SR Serbia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<span style=\"display:none\">015</span>15th\n|-\n|[[NK Olimpija Ljubljana (1911)|Olimpija]]\n|[[Ljubljana]]\n|{{flag|SR Slovenia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<span style=\"display:none\">011</span>11th\n|-\n|[[FK Partizan|Partizan]]\n|[[Belgrade]]\n|{{flag|SR Serbia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<span style=\"display:none\">002</span>2nd\n|-\n|[[FK Proleter Zrenjanin|Proleter Zrenjanin]]\n|[[Zrenjanin]]\n|{{flag|SR Serbia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<span style=\"display:none\">008</span>8th\n|-\n|[[FK Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161|Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161]]\n|[[Ni\u0161]]\n|{{flag|SR Serbia}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<span style=\"display:none\">009</span>9th\n|-\n|[[Red Star Belgrade|